2. In these Regulations, unless the context otherwise r e q u i r e s
      "approved training institution" means an institution approved by the
           Council as a school for training dental auxiliaries;
      "Board of Examiners" means the Board of Examiners established
           under regulation 13;
      "Dental Auxiliary Training School" means the Dental Auxiliary
          Training School established by the Government;
      "enrolled member" means a person enrolled under the Act as a
           member in any prescribed class of dental auxiliary;
      "recognized university" or "recognized college" means a university or
           college respectively, offering courses of training, degrees, and
           other qualifications which is declared to be such by the Council;
      "registered member" means a person registered under the Act as a
            dentist.
